glosses: to plant (plants only, for seeds see ekmek)

examples.text: Boş toprağa bir koru dikseniz otuz yılda gölge verir.
examples.translation: If you were to plant trees in empty soil, [they would grow large enough] in 30 years to provide a nice shadow.

examples.text: Doldurmasıyla kadehini dikmesi, gözünü kırpmadan tek yudumda devirmesi bir oluyor.
examples.translation: He instantaneously refills his cup and chugs his drink in a single breath, without even blinking.

glosses: to assign a person to a place to guard

examples.text: O günden sonra kapıya diktiği bir bekçiye iş çıkışları işçilerin üstlerini arattı.
examples.translation: From that day onwards he made the guard whom he assigned at the entrance search the workers after work.

glosses: to kick a ball directly upwards

examples.text: maç yapan çocukların topunu havaya dikmek
examples.translation: to kick the ball of the kids playing soccer up in the air

examples.text: Biz apartman dikmek için ağaçları kese duralım, İsviçre'de içinde küçük bir orman olan gökdelen yapıyorlar.
examples.translation: As we go on cutting the trees to build apartments, in Switzerand they are building a skyscraper with a tiny forest in it.

glosses: to place the ball somewhere on the field

examples.text: Top toplayıcıdan gelen topu köşe noktasına dikti.
examples.translation: He placed the ball coming from the ball boy on the corner area.

glosses: to sew, to sew up, to stitch, to stitch up

examples.translation: How to sew up torn jeans?

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish دیكمك (dikmek), from Proto-Turkic *tik-.
